{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "To approximate the action-value functions, the authors used Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) on the representations of environment states obtained from the video game frames without any prior information regarding the games, no manually extracted features, and no knowledge regarding the internal state of the ALE emulator.",
    "Thus, agent learning occurred only from video inputs, reward signals, the set of possible actions, and the final state information of each game.",
    "The authors attributed their state-of-the-art results mainly to the ability of their CNN to represent the games' states.",
    "Mnih et al. (2015) improved DQN by changing how CNN is used, as shown in Algorithm 1.",
    "Instead of using the same network (with the same parameters Θ) to approximate both the action-value function Q(s, a, Θ) and the target action-value function Q(s, a, Θ), the authors used independent sets of parameters Θ and Θ for each network."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Mnih et al. (2015) improved DQN by changing how CNN is used, as shown in Algorithm 1."
  ]
}